arch:note.arch:string: The purpose of the daily journal was to record the activities taking place in a trench each day. This included which loci were excavated, how and why loci were excavated and the ongoing impressions of the relationships among loci. It should be noted that journals record the actions, impressions and ideas of trench supervisors during the excavations. They are not, therefore, the final interpretations or syntheses of the emerging data.

arch:internalDocument.arch:string:
July 24, 2001

We sweeped the trench and then we started to finish the part in L4014 until the rocks.

We sprayed the trench and the wall L4030 was very obvious. We saw that the other wall in the NE1/4 was not that obvious there but we can still see it as different. Because it is more crumbly and the surrounding is more smooth.

We took the rock out from L4031 that was sitting inside the oven.

Also we started to level L4034 with the surrounding. There are still more pebbles and some more pottery. (the reason that I am continuing as the see locus here)

We will take L4011 out and close it if nothing changes. Because in L4014 we found some pebble feature that might be connected with this locus. There was a huge sand stone/slag like stone at the bottom which is huge. (crumbly/yellowish/flat/smooth)

We are now articulating L4015 more. But it seems that there is only one row of rocks aligned and a collapse at the W side of it. (Possibly from the alignment when there were more rows there.)

We took off L4012 out. There were big rocks too. (up to 50 cm wide)(River rocks) There were at the bottom level mud brick like/ river conglomerate/ slag like rocks.

Now we are taking off L4015 after taking the photos. Because of the alignment it seems like a wall but also with the collapse from the wall. OR: It might be a surface because of the pottery sitting on the upper elevation so I marked it as a feature.

Then we started to articulate L4024 and we found a nice base that we KT as 4207. After this I think Pete will continue digging in the NW part of the trench because in C1 baulk section we saw a surface that we will try to catch here.

Now Peter will continue digging C4.I will dig the side of the trench just uphill from C1. I start by removing the artificial baulk on the W center which is call that should be left of L4001, so that should get closed today.
